  <a name="a_portfolio"></a>
  <div id="portfolio" class="section3 content area">
    <div class="title">
      <p>Click below to view the case study</p>
    </div>

    <div id="case-studies">
      <a href="/projects/fuze.html">
        <div class="case type square fadein">
          <div class="thumb">
            <%= image_tag '/images/clients/fuze.svg', class: "fuze" %>
          </div>
          <div class="description">
            <p>
              Fuze is a collaboration product that integrates HD audio and video meetings with rich content sharing. I was
              tasked to help recreate Fuze from the ground up by working directly with a team of product managers and developers
              (local and remote) on a variety of platforms. An undertaking that required not only getting
              close with users but also working with the development team to ensure the success of the apps.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/projects/vulume.html">
        <div class="case type square">
          <div class="thumb vulume">
            <%= image_tag '/images/clients/vulume.svg', class: "vulume" %>
          </div>
          <div class="description">
            <p> Vulume is a project collaboration, sharing, and discovery tool for the Built Environment, working to transform the way
              architects and designers collaborate and work with clients and contractors. Their target user group's work style was
              set in the old ways of physical documents, on-site meetings, and endless email chains -- we aimed to disrupt that.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/projects/htf.html">
        <div class="case type square">
          <div class="thumb">
            <%= image_tag '/images/clients/htf.svg', class: "htf" %>
          </div>
          <div class="description">
            <p> Hack the Future is a series of self-directed hackathons for future hackers from 5th-12th grade.
              It’s a unique opportunity for youngsters to learn modern software and hardware engineering from mentors in bay
              area startups and companies. I handled the creation of branding the event as well as serve
              as a design mentor for the kids. </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

